PN,30201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775873035
OL,3,CFirst manned Moon mission in more than
OL,4,C50 years splashes down after epic
OL,5,Cvoyage
OL,7,FNasa astronauts have landed safely
OL,8,Fback on Earth following their record-
OL,9,Fbreaking lunar flyby which marks a
OL,10,Fstepping stone towards a future Moon
OL,11,Flanding and eventual Mars mission.
OL,13,FThe Artemis II crew splashed down off
OL,14,Fthe coast of San Diego in California
OL,15,Fat 1.07am UK time and Nasa said the
OL,16,Ffour crew members ` Commander Reid
OL,17,FWiseman, pilot Victor Glover,
OL,18,FChristina Koch and Canadian Jeremy
OL,19,FHansen ` were healthy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775873035
OL,3,CFirst manned Moon mission in more than
OL,4,C50 years splashes down after epic
OL,5,Cvoyage
OL,7,FMission Control's Rob Navias described
OL,8,Ftheir return as "a perfect bullseye
OL,9,Fsplashdown".
OL,11,FDuring re-entry, their Orion capsule
OL,12,Fwas expected to hit the atmosphere at
OL,13,Faround 24,000mph (38,625kph), or about
OL,14,F32 times the speed of sound.
OL,16,FIn a critical test for the
OL,17,Fspacecraft's heat shield, temperatures
OL,18,Foutside were set to soar to as high as
OL,19,F2,760C (5,000F).
OL,26,@pD@QOUqD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775873035
OL,3,CFirst manned Moon mission in more than
OL,4,C50 years splashes down after epic
OL,5,Cvoyage
OL,7,FFollowing a previous test flight,
OL,8,Fengineers had altered the descent
OL,9,Ftrajectory in order to reduce the risk
OL,10,Fof the module burning up.
OL,12,FThe intensity of the return meant
OL,13,Fcontact with the crew was cut off for
OL,14,Fseveral minutes, prior to the
OL,15,Fdeployment of parachutes eventually
OL,16,Fslowing the capsule's fall to just
OL,17,F17mph (27 kph) before hitting the
OL,18,Fwater.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775873035
OL,3,CFirst manned Moon mission in more than
OL,4,C50 years splashes down after epic
OL,5,Cvoyage
OL,7,FThe naval ship USS John P Murtha and a
OL,8,Ffleet of military aircraft were
OL,9,Fstanding by to help recover the crew
OL,10,Fone by one, which was expected to take
OL,11,Fabout an hour.
OL,13,FThe first manned Moon mission in more
OL,14,Fthan 50 years, which blasted off from
OL,15,FCape Canaveral on April 1, took the
OL,16,Fthree Americans and a Canadian deeper
OL,17,Finto space than anyone has gone before.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775873035
OL,3,CFirst manned Moon mission in more than
OL,4,C50 years splashes down after epic
OL,5,Cvoyage
OL,7,FThe crew travelled 252,756 miles
OL,8,F(406,771 kilometres) from Earth,
OL,9,Fsmashing the distance milestone of
OL,10,F248,655 miles (400,171 kilometres)
OL,11,Fpreviously held by the Apollo 13 crew
OL,12,Ffor 56 years.
OL,14,FTheir epic voyage took them around the
OL,15,Ffar side of the Moon, normally hidden
OL,16,Fto the human eye, which included a 40-
OL,17,Fminute communication blackout when
OL,18,Fthey were cut off entirely from their
OL,19,Fhome planet.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
